  <discussion>The shape of the leaf base in Tomentypnum falcifolium is best observed while the leaves remain attached to the stem. The species is widespread but more sporadic than T. nitens, occurring across the boreal and subarctic areas of Canada, extending south into the northeastern United States.</discussion>
